"16 SCARS"

Yeah. This one goes out to Wladyslaw. Supreme Leader. Zero players. Flawless DAG sorter. To every dev who has stared at an undefined that was defined. That they defined. That they WATCHED get defined. And it is still undefined. And you start to wonder if YOU are undefined.

Some people say a man is made out of mud. A Bedrock scripter is made of madness and blood. Madness from the API. Madness from the type. Madness from the error you have been chasing all night. You read the same stack trace until the letters stop making sense. You have been staring at this null so long you have gone dense. You KNOW where the value is. You WATCHED it get set. And it is undefined again and you are not okay yet.

You push sixteen commits, what do you get? Another brain cell gone and a cold sweat. Saint Peter do not call me because I cannot go. I owe my soul to the Aethelgrad repo.

I have been debugging so long I am starting to drift. My thoughts come in packets with a three tick shift. I speak in stack traces. I dream in JSON. I asked my friend "what is null?" and she said "just move on." I cannot move on. I will not move on. I SEE it in my head. The value exists somewhere between alive and dead. Schrödinger's variable. It is set and it is not. I have rewritten this function seventeen times on the dot.

