The journal was bleeding. The ledger was wrong. I had been staring at transactions so long I had gone numb and gone strong. Gone numb in the eyes. Gone strong in the hate. For a flush that ran early and corrupted the state. I started talking to the code like it could hear me speak. "Why are you writing his data into her account this week?" The code said nothing. The code never does. I patched it with flushKeys through the madness and the buzz.

I have read this line of output about forty seven times. object Object. It haunts me like a nursery rhyme. I KNOW what you are. You are a Player. You are a SOUL. But Bedrock handed you to me as a C++ black hole. I called toString. I called name. I called id. I called things that do not exist just to feel something. And then I sat in silence for a very long while and wrote a wrapper function and I did not even smile.

